<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                    <head>No. 145.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-09-29"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 29, 1887</date>.
                            (Received November 25.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 464.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the third
                        installment of the indemnity fund (6,000 taels) to the American missionaries
                        was paid to Mr. Cockburn, <pb facs="0354" n="220" xml:id="pg_220"/> Her
                        Britannic Majesty’s consular agent at Chung King, the 3d instant. This sum
                        has been placed by Mr. Cockburn in the Hong Kong and Shanghai Bank at Hankow
                        to the credit of Dr. Crews.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles
                            Denby.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>